The paper deals with the edge-coloring problem in the message-passing model of distributed computing, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the vertex-coloring problem and introduces a new family of graphs with bounded neighborhood independence, which falls under the category of graph theory (cs.GT). The algorithmic techniques used in the paper involve analyzing the time complexity of the algorithms, which falls under the category of algorithms (cs.AL). The paper also discusses the maximum degree of the input graph, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper introduces a new algorithm for vertex-coloring graphs with bounded neighborhood independence, which falls under the category of network information theory (cs.NI).
